    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our offensive engine is headlined by **Daulton Varsho** (69.94) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (69.81), both of whom clear the 69-point threshold as our most efficient starts. **Daulton Varsho** benefits from a high-ceiling matchup against Woods Richardson, with a +19% bump from the starter's expected ERA and a favorable platoon advantage. Similarly, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains a staple; his score is elevated by an exceptionally hitter-friendly park factor (+10%) and his ability to exploit the slow delivery of Ginn, which keeps his stolen base potential firmly in play. **Tyler Freeman** (69.01) rounds out our elite tier, buoyed significantly by a +14% park factor that makes him a high-leverage start despite a mid-tier batting order spot.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved **Yainer Diaz** (47.40), who sat on the bubble but ultimately fell behind **Cal Raleigh** (50.44) and **Will Smith** (59.61). While **Yainer Diaz** offers a favorable park factor, his negative SP efficiency score against Bennett rendered him a marginal play compared to the higher order stability of **Cal Raleigh** at #2. We are also monitoring the speed-focused dynamics of the bottom half of our lineup; **Bryson Stott** (60.16) remains a prioritized start specifically due to his +4% efficiency boost derived from a slow pitcher delivery, aligning perfectly with our strategy to capitalize on stolen base opportunities in this 5x5 format.\n\nRisk management dictates caution regarding the heavy-lefty exposure against McClanahan, who creates a challenging environment for **Luis Arraez** (51.14), **Jung Hoo Lee** (45.43), and **Matt Chapman** (53.36). While all three remain in the lineup, their scores are depressed by the combination of a tough SP and neutral-to-negative platoon impacts. We continue to monitor the weather for the later games to ensure that our bench depth\u2014including **Masyn Winn**, **Lawrence Butler**, **Jonathan Aranda**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert**\u2014remains ready should any late-inning tactical shifts or weather delays force a substitution to protect our daily game caps.",
